name: Trading
description: Logic for the trading contract which specifies the main parameters of the protocol

name: Oracle
description: Logic for the oracle contract which gets the price data for different assets

name: Treasury
description: Logic for the treasury which is where the part of the fees that belong to the protocol accrue

name: Pool ETH
description: Logic for the ETH pool. Users can deposit ETH to this pool and in exchange earn a portion of trader losses and fees based on the users share of the pool

name: Pool USDC
description: Logic for the USDC pool. Users can deposit USDC to this pool and in exchange earn a portion of trader losses and fees based on the users share of the pool

name: Pool Rewards ETH
description: Logic for the ETH reward pool. This is where the fees paid by users accrue

name: Pool Rewards USDC
description: Logic for the USDC reward pool. This is where the fees paid by users accrue

name: Pool CAP
description: Logic for the CAP pool. Users can deposit CAP to this pool and in exchange earn a portion of trader fees based on the users share of the pool

name: CAP Rewards ETH
description: Logic for the CAP ETH reward pool. This is where the fees paid in ETH by users that go to CAP stakers are held

name: CAP Rewards USDC
description: Logic for the CAP USDC reward pool. This is where the fees paid in USDC by users that go to CAP stakers are held

name: CAP Token
description: Logic for the CAP governance token

name: CAP Token (Arbitrum)
description: Logic for the CAP governance token (Arbitrum)
